# 15.6 Triple Integral

These are legit just double integrals taken to the next step. Instead of using $dA$ we use $dV$
$$\int\int_D\int f(x,y,z)\ dV$$
We follow the same rules involving integration over rectangular regions as well as integration over general regions.

### Example

Evalute $\int\int\int_E z\ dV$
On the bonded surface $z=12xy$ and the bonded plane $y=x,x=1$

Step 1. Draw out integral
$$\int^1_0\int^x_0\int^{12xy}_0z\ dz\ dy\ dx$$
Step 2. Inside Integral
$$\int^{12xy}_0z\ dz$$
$$=72x^2y^2$$
Step 3. Middle Integral
$$\int^x_072x^2y^2\ dy$$
$$=24x^5$$
Step 4. Outside Integral
$$\int^1_024x^5\ dx$$
$$=4$$
